<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1849-08-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1849-08-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="236" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d236">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Preston</persName>,
                                    Secretary of the Navy, to Commodore <persName type="to">Downes</persName>, United States Navy.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Navy
                                    Department</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1849-08-21"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 21,
                                1849</date>.</dateline>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The inclosed packet, addressed to
                                Commander Charles Lowndes, commanding the United States ship
                                Germantown, you will be pleased to have delivered to him with all
                                practicable dispatch. His services with the vessel under his command
                                are required under confidential instructions; you will therefore be
                                pleased to facilitate his movements by affording every aid in your
                                power *to hasten his departure from Boston. <seg type="margin">[685]</seg></p>
                            <p>I am, very respectfully, yours, &amp;c.,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <list>
                                        <item>WM. BALLARD PRESTON.</item>
                                        <item>Commodore <hi rend="smallcaps">John
                                                Downes</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Commandant United
                                                States Navy-Yard, Boston</hi>.</item>
                                    </list>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>